Senate Transportation and Safety 1
Amendment No. 1 to SB1591
Massey
Signature of Sponsor
AMEND S e n ate Bill No. 1591* House Bill No. 1555
by deleting all language after the enacting clause and substituting:
SECTION 1. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 55-8-199(c)(1), is amended by
deleting the third and fourth sentences and substituting instead:
Notwithstanding § 8-21-401(g)(1) or another law to the contrary, a person violating this
section is subject to court costs not to exceed fifty percent (50%) of the standard court
cost charged by the court for a case involving a traffic citation as well as state and local
litigation taxes.
SECTION 2. This act takes effect July 1, 2026, the public welfare requiring it, and
applies to violations occurring on or after such date.
